'''Yunus Akgün''' (born 7 July 2000) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[winger (association football)|right winger]] for {{Turkish football updater|Galatasaray}} club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Early life==
Yunus Akgün was born on July 7, 2000, into a family of four in the [[Küçükçekmece]] district of [[Istanbul]]. His mother is a homemaker, while his father previously worked in a factory and later took on a supportive role in his son’s career. He has a younger brother, born in 2008, who is also involved in football and has played for Akgün’s former youth club, [[Kosova Güç Spor]]. Akgün’s family background includes roots in [[Kastamonu]] on his mother’s side, while his father is of [[Albanians|Albanian]] descent.<ref>{{cite news 
 |title=Yunus Akgün'den geleceğiyle ilgili açıklama: "Her oyuncunun hayali Avrupa'da oynamak ama ben..." 
|url=https://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/spor/yunus-akgun-den-gelecegiyle-ilgili-aciklama-her-oyuncunun-hayali-avrupa-da-oynamak-ama-ben-2487327 
 |work=Cumhuriyet 
 |date=16 March 2026 
 |access-date=19 March 2026 
 |language=tr 
}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Galatasaray===
Akgün is a product of the [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] youth academy, joining in 2011. He made his professional debut for Galatasaray in the 2018 [[Turkish Super Cup]] 1–1 (5–4) penalty shootout loss against [[Akhisar Belediyespor]] on 5 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=267&ftxtID=29706|title=Galatasaray 1-1 AkhisarsporNormal süre sona erdi – Kupalar TFF|website=tff.org}}</ref>
On 29 January 2019, Akgün scored a [[hat-trick]] in 4–1 win of [[Turkish Cup]] match against [[Boluspor]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Galatasaray'da Yunus Akgün fırtınası! Hat-trick yaptı, maç topunu aldı |url=https://www.sabah.com.tr/galeri/spor/galatasarayda-yunus-akgun-firtinasi-hat-trick-yapti-mac-topunu-aldi |website=Sabah |language=tr}}</ref>

====Adana Demirspor (loan)====
On 6 September 2021, [[Adana Demirspor]] brought in Akgün on a loan from [[Galatasaray]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Yunus Akgün'ün Adana Demirspor'a geçici transferi hakkında |url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/kulup/yunus-akgunun-adana-demirspora-gecici-transferi-hakkinda/49292 |publisher=Galatasaray S.K. |access-date=6 September 2021}}</ref>

====Return to Galatasaray after loan====
Akgün became the champion in the [[Süper Lig]] in the [[2022–23 Süper Lig|2022–23]] season with the [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] team. Defeating [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]] 4–1 away in the match played in the 36th week on 30 May 2023, Galatasaray secured the lead with two weeks before the end and won the 23rd championship in its history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517|title=Turkish Super Lig: Galatasaray win title for 23rd time after beating Ankaragucu 4–1|website=BBC Sport|date=30 May 2023|access-date=31 May 2023}}</ref>

====Leicester City (loan)====
On 26 August 2023, [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] signed Akgün on loan for the [[2023–24 EFL Championship|2023–24]] season.<ref>{{cite news |title=About the temporary transfer of our football player Yunus Akgün |url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/futbolcumuz-yunus-akgunun-gecici-transferi-hakkinda/53812 |publisher=Galatasaray SK |date=26 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Leicester City Confirm Loan Signing Of Yunus Akgün |url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/3653491/leicester-city-confirm-loan-signing-of-yunus-akgn |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |date=26 August 2023}}</ref> He made his debut for the club three days later in a 2–0 away win against [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] in the second round of the [[EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Carabao Cup: Tranmere Rovers 0–2 Leicester City – Jamie Vardy scores as Foxes reach third round |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66577639|website=BBC Sport|date=29 August 2023}}</ref> On 27 January 2024, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–0 home win against [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] in the fourth round of the [[FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=FA Cup: Leicester City 3–0 Birmingham City – Jamie Vardy helps Foxes reach fifth round|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68110784|website=BBC Sport|date=27 January 2024}}</ref>

====Return to Galatasaray after second loan====
After a successful summer at [[Euro 2024]], Akgün had a promising start to the [[2024–25 Galatasaray S.K. season|2024–25]] season with Galatasaray. As of mid-October 2024, he had played 13 matches across all competitions, scoring 5 goals and providing 1 assist. In addition to his goal contributions, Akgün showed versatility by playing both wings and has been a regular starter in both the [[Süper Lig]] and [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] matches. This strong form has allowed him to cement his position as a key player for Galatasaray, filling in after key departures like [[Kerem Aktürkoğlu]] and [[Wilfried Zaha]].

On August 5, 2025, it was announced that his contract was extended until the end of the 2028–29 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 August 2025 |title=Yeni Sözleşme Yunus Akgün |url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/yeni-sozlesme-yunus-akgun/58262 |access-date=5 August 2025 |website=Galatasaray S.K.}}</ref>

==International career==
Akgün is a youth international for Turkey. He represented the [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey U17]]s at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]],<ref>{{cite web|title=U17 Milliler, Hırvatistan'daki ilk antrenmanını yaptı|url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=276&ftxtID=27063|website=www.tff.org|language=tr}}</ref> and the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=276&ftxtID=27865 |publisher=Türkiye Futbol Federasyonu |title=U17 Milli Takımı, Dünya Kupası hazırlıklarına başladı |date=16 September 2017 |language=tr |access-date=16 September 2017 }}</ref>

Akgün made his senior debut for Turkey on 4 June 2022, in a [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] tie at home to the [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Player details TFF|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=526&kisiId=1442892|website=www.tff.org|language=tr}}</ref> Akgün scored his first senior level goal for Turkey on the occasion of his second cap, scoring the fifth goal of six away to [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]] on 7 June 2022 in another UEFA Nations League tie.<ref>{{cite web|title=Player details TFF|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=526&kisiId=1442892|website=tff.org|language=tr}}</ref>

He was named in Turkey's 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=18 June 2024}}</ref>

